dcterms:creator: D. Bankman
dcterms:description: A dataset containing designs for a two-stage transimpedance amplifier, used for evaluating performance metrics such as bandwidth, gain, power, noise, and peaking.
dcterms:title: Two-Stage Transimpedance Amplifier

dcterms:creator: D. Bankman
dcterms:description: A dataset containing designs for a two-stage voltage amplifier, focusing on metrics such as bandwidth, common mode phase margin, differential mode phase margin, power, noise, and open loop gain.
dcterms:title: Two-Stage Voltage Amplifier

dcterms:creator: D. Bankman
dcterms:description: A dataset containing designs for a three-stage transimpedance amplifier, used to evaluate performance metrics including bandwidth, gain, and power.
dcterms:title: Three-Stage Transimpedance Amplifier

dcterms:creator: D. Bankman
dcterms:description: A dataset containing designs for a low-dropout regulator (LDO), focusing on metrics such as settling time, load regulation, and power supply rejection ratio.
dcterms:title: Low-Dropout Regulator (LDO)

dcterms:creator: B. Murmann
dcterms:description: A dataset containing designs for a two-stage transimpedance amplifier, used in the Stanford EE214B Advanced Analog IC Design Contest.
dcterms:title: Two-TIA

dcterms:creator: B. Murmann
dcterms:description: A dataset containing designs for a three-stage transimpedance amplifier, used in the Stanford EE214B Advanced Analog IC Design Contest.
dcterms:title: Three-TIA
